						               													<description>Think Thrice consists of 25 tiles, each with three attributes: the foreground color (red, yellow, or blue); the background color (green, violet, or orange); and the shape of the picture on the tile (sun, moon, or star).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player begins the game with four tiles. On his turn, a player either draws a tile from the bag or plays one or more tiles to the playing area to form one or more triads. A triad is a set of three tiles in which either an attribute is the same on all three tiles or it is different on all three tiles, as in the game of Set.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In making a play, a player may link his tiles to existing ones in the playing area or keep them separate. He also may re-arrange previously played tiles, provided that every tile in the playing area remains part of a triad.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to run out of tiles wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
